During a visit to Chile, Vice President Mike Pence reaffirmed the strategic partnership between the United States and Chile. He praised Chile for its economic success and free-market reforms, and highlighted the strong trade relationship between the two countries. Pence also discussed regional security issues, including the nuclear threat from North Korea and the political crisis in Venezuela. He called on Chile and other Latin American countries to cut diplomatic and commercial ties with North Korea, and urged greater support for the restoration of democracy in Venezuela. Pence concluded by expressing confidence in the future progress and cooperation between the United States and Chile.